<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
A culture of innovation is at the heart of everything we do. This stems from a commitment for continuous improvement and a desire to remain at the forefront of the world&#39;s financial markets. As technology evolves, the knowledge and skill set of associates within technology must also evolve, enabling us to continue to develop and deliver the multi&ndash;platform, multi&ndash;product range for which we are renowned.
</p>
<p class="bac">
The company&#39;s strategic vision is to deliver market&ndash;leading technology that drives our business forward. Our teams work very closely with our business partners, developing strategies and delivering solutions that are integral to the day&ndash;to&ndash;day running of our business. Technology embraces everything from sales, trading and research applications, trade processing, risk management, portfolio management, payment services, voice recognition, and quantitative and qualitative analysis, to security analytics, management reporting and stakeholder relationship management.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
The Summer Analyst Program within Technology is a precursor to the Technology Analyst Full&ndash;Time Program. Summer Analysts are given a true associate experience, as internships mirror full&ndash;time positions, and include goal&ndash;setting and a formal review process. You can be placed in one of the following roles, according to your skill set:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li><b>Business Analyst:</b>&nbsp;Translate business needs into technical requirements, documenting process flows and producing diagrams to ensure understanding amongst all project team members</li>
	<li><b>Developer:</b>&nbsp;Provide technical excellence to design, develop and maintain state&ndash;of&ndash;the&ndash;art technology applications, utilizing technologies such as Java/EJB&#39;s, C++, .NET and Web services. Responsible for internal and external client requirements gathering, translating client interactions into technical design specifications, business process reengineering, and partnering with business, product and technology teams across the company to deliver world&ndash;class technology solutions  </li>
	<li><b>Project Management or Systems Support Engineer:</b>&nbsp;Provide management, administration and configuration of proprietary applications, and 3rd party solutions for application servers, messaging, monitoring, etc.</li>
	<li><b>Quality Assurance:</b>&nbsp;Combine financial, business and technical knowledge, to develop comprehensive test strategies for internally&ndash;developed trading systems. Development of knowledge in all these areas is encouraged and supported.</li>
	<li><b>Quantitative Analyst:</b>&nbsp;Develop sophisticated models, analyses and forecasts supporting pricing and risk management for a range of financial securities</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
As a Technology Summer Analyst, you&#39;ll:  
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Work as a developer, tester, systems support analyst or business analyst within a fast&ndash;paced, innovative environment</li>
	<li>Have a rich and varied working experience</li>
	<li>Work closely with colleagues throughout our organisation to build relationships</li>
	<li>Gain the knowledge and expertise to meet the challenges critical to building a technology career within the financial services industry</li>
	<li>Collaborate on exciting global projects that contribute to business success and next&ndash;generation advances </li>
	<li>Be exposed to a broad range of technologies covering many diverse environments: 
        <ul>
	<li>Applications development, involving the design, development and deployment of state&ndash;of&ndash;the&ndash;art applications using Java, C++, .NET and Web Services, to power and improve our business</li>
	<li>Business analysis, using key client&ndash;facing skills and deep technical expertise to bridge business and technology and create powerful specifications</li>
	<li>Project and delivery management, bringing new applications online using Waterfall and Agile development lifecycle methodologies</li>
        </ul></li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Placement:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
Summer Analysts participate in a 10&ndash;12 week program, based in Singapore, Hong Kong, India or Japan, providing a unique opportunity and exposure to life as a technologist. Summer Analysts are placed directly with a specific team throughout the internship.  
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Strong academic qualifications are important, but you&#39;ll also need to demonstrate drive, innovation and a genuine interest in a technology career within financial markets. We accept applications from a diverse range of degree disciplines, although Computer Science and Engineering subjects are key for this line of business. Working knowledge of Java and/or C++ is essential. You&#39;ll also need teamwork, leadership and problem&ndash;solving skills, plus creativity, and the ability to work in a fast&ndash;paced environment, multi&ndash;task and interact with a variety of people.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
The best opportunity to learn about working life at the bank is to experience it first&ndash;hand through our Summer Program. Aimed at students in their penultimate year, the program is designed to help you decide whether our offering matches your aspirations. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
You&#39;ll be assigned to one of our core technology groups that support our businesses, such as Wealth Management or Rates &#38; Currencies. Working on real tasks, problems, issues or projects alongside our technologists will give you a unique learning opportunity and exposure to life at a leading investment bank.
</p>
<p class="bac">
The program includes:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Relevant continuous training sessions over the internship period </li>
	<li>Opportunities to interact with senior technologists and network with peers</li>
	<li>A buddy program</li>
	<li>Constructive feedback sessions through performance evaluations</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
If you perform well during your time, you may go back to university with a job offer for the following year, enabling you to truly focus on your studies.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Locations:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Singapore, Hong Kong, India or Japan
</p>

